// For Writing C Code 

1) Use IDE Geny(Pre installed on Raspberry PI)(Fie -> New(with template) -> Main.c to open predefined c file)

2) Use IDE NetBeans (Professional, Can run on Mac, Window, Linux)(You can install it on Mac/Window and connect it to Raspberry Pi remotly)

Note: 
1) IDE Geny, Monodev and Netbeans(slow) can be installed on Raspberry PI
2) ON IDE NetBeans and MS Visual Studio + Visual GDB you can work on mac/Winow and connect to raspberry Pi remotly

